[SN]TITLE[SN]
Two held after man stabbed in neck in Barrow

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man is recovering in hospital after being stabbed in the neck in Barrow.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 49-year-old had already lost a "significant" amount of blood when police found him in a flat at Egerton Court at about 19:00 GMT on Friday.
He was taken to Furness General Hospital then transferred to hospital in Preston where his condition is described as stable.
A man, 58, and woman, 45, both from Barrow, have been arrested on suspicion of grievous bodily harm.
